edu.udel.cis.taschd.time

Class TimeInterval

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.udel.cis.taschd.time.TimeInterval
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TimeInterval>

    public class TimeInterval
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<TimeInterval>

    TimeInterval represents a single TimeInterval within a week. A TimeInterval begins at a certain minute in the week, and has a duration, measured in minutes. This class is immutable.

    For now, a TimeInterval will simply wrap a String, it uses nothing.

        startHour - the hour of the day in which the TimeInterval begins, an integer in the range [0,24).
        startMinute - the minute of the hour in which the TimeInterval begins, an integer in the range [0,60).
        duration - the duration of the TimeInterval, in minutes, an interval in the range [0,1440].

      • minutesAfter

        public int minutesAfter(TimeInterval that)
        Computes the number of minutes between the end of that TimeInterval and the beginning of this one. This assumes that the TimeIntervals are repeated every week, infinitely into the past and future, so that this difference is always defined.
        Parameters:
        that - another (non-null) TimeInterval.
        Returns:
        the number of minutes between the end of that TimeInterval and the beginning of the next occurrence of this TimeInterval; always a non-negative integer.

      • compareStart

        public int compareStart(TimeInterval that)
        Compares the start times of this TimeInterval with that one. Returns -1, 0, or 1 depending on whether this starts earlier, same time, or later than that
        Parameters:
        that - another non-null TimeInterval.
        Returns:
        -1 if this one starts at earlier time in the week; 0 if the starts times are equal; +1 if this one starts at a later time in the week.

      • compareEnd

        public int compareEnd(TimeInterval that)
        Compares the end times of this TimeInterval with that one. Returns -1, 0, or 1 depending on whether this ends earlier, same time, or later than that.
        Parameters:
        that - another non-null TimeInterval.
        Returns:
        -1 if this one ends at earlier time in the week; 0 if the end times are equal; +1 if this one ends at a later time in the week.
